115 A.3d 1261 In the Matter of the APPLICATION OF Omeed TABIEI for Admission to the Bar of Maryland. Misc. No. 39

Sept. Term 2014.

Court of Appeals of Maryland. June 5, 2015.

BARBERA, C.J, HARRELL, BATTAGLIA, GREENE, adkins, McDonald, watts, jj.

ORDER

The Court having considered the recommendations of the Character Committee for the Fourth Appellate Circuit of Maryland and the State Board of Law Examiners, and the oral argument of the applicant’s counsel presented at a hearing held before this Court on June 4, 2015, it is this 5th day of June, 2015,

ORDERED, by the Court of Appeals of Maryland, with a majority concurring, that the favorable recommendations of the Character Committee for the Fourth Appellate Circuit, and of the State Board of Law Examiners be, and are hereby accepted, and it is further

ORDERED, that the applicant, upon taking the oath prescribed by the statute, be admitted to the practice of law in this State.
